---
import DocsLayout from "../layouts/DocsLayout.astro";
---

<DocsLayout title="Changelog" description="physure release history and version changes" activeSection="changelog">
  <div class="page-header">
    <div class="kicker">Release History</div>
    <h1>Changelog</h1>
    <p>Version history and release notes for physure.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="callout callout-info">
    <p>physure is currently in <strong>Beta</strong>. The API may change between versions before the 1.0 stable release.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="releases">

    <div class="release current">
      <div class="release-header">
        <h2 id="v022">
          <span class="release-version">v0.2.2</span>
          <span class="badge badge-green">Latest</span>
          <span class="release-date">2026</span>
        </h2>
      </div>
      <div class="release-body">
        <h3>What's new</h3>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Standalone Native Rust PHS Engine (<code>phs</code>)</strong>: Pure Rust interpreter executable with zero Python dependencies. Supports script execution (<code>phs file.phs</code>), CLI evaluation (<code>phs "500 N / 2 m^2 => kPa"</code>), and standalone terminal REPL.</li>
          <li><strong>VS Code Extension <code>vsc-physure 0.2.2</code></strong>: Launches native <code>phs</code> executable directly, native REPL terminal, <code>physure-lsp</code> high-performance Rust language server, shebang detection (<code>#!/usr/bin/env phs</code>), and <code>Physure: New PHS File</code> command.</li>
          <li><strong>PyO3 Native Bridge</strong>: Fast PyO3 FFI bridge (<code>physure._core.evaluate_phs_native</code>) exposing the Rust PHS evaluator directly to Python host applications.</li>
          <li><strong>Display Text & Multiline Blocks</strong>: Full support for verbatim Markdown display text blocks (<code>```...```</code>) and indented multiline function bodies in PHS grammar.</li>
          <li><strong>Vector & Uncertainty Builtins</strong>: Element-wise vector power and division (<code>Vector ^ 2</code>, <code>k * q / Vector^2</code>), <code>linspace</code>, <code>plot</code>, and uncertainty literal propagation (<code>+/-</code>).</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Install</h3>
        <pre><code>cargo install --path physure-core --bin phs  # Native binary
pip install physure                           # Python package
code --install-extension vsc-physure-0.2.2.vsix # VS Code Extension</code></pre>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="release">
      <div class="release-header">
        <h2 id="v018">
          <span class="release-version">v0.1.8</span>
          <span class="release-date">2026</span>
        </h2>
      </div>
      <div class="release-body">
        <h3>What's new</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Chemistry extension added under <code>physure.ext.chemistry</code>: Species formula parsing, automatic stoichiometric reaction balancing, theoretical yields, kinetics, and thermodynamic free energy checks</li>
          <li>Native Symbolic Engine (<code>physure.domain.symbolic.native.Expr</code>): Zero-dependency algebraic simplification (<code>.simplify()</code>) and analytical differentiation (<code>.diff()</code>) with Rust core backend and pure-Python fallback</li>
          <li>Ahead-of-Time Physics Compiler (<code>physure.ext.compiler</code>): <code>compile_physics_model</code> traces and verifies formulas, baking them into high-speed unitless raw-float kernels</li>
          <li>Symbolic Regression (<code>physure.ext.symbolic_regression</code>): <code>SymbolicRegressor</code> fits physically valid formulas to empirical data using genetic programming</li>
          <li>Unit-Aware Plotting (<code>physure.plotting</code>): <code>plot()</code>, <code>plot_slices()</code>, and <code>plot_covariance()</code> with automatic axis labels, error bars, and covariance visualization</li>
          <li>Python 3.13 and 3.14 support added to CI matrix</li>
          <li>Improved startup performance — import budget tracked in CI</li>
          <li>GrammarInterpreter: added <code>= ?</code> query syntax for variable inspection</li>
          <li><code>physure repl</code> now accepts an inline expression argument</li>
          <li>CODATA 2022 constants updated — 400+ physical constants available</li>
          <li>Rust core (<code>physure-core</code>) updated for PyO3 0.22 compatibility</li>
          <li>Pandas integration improved: better dtype handling for quantity columns</li>
          <li>Test coverage gate raised to 80%+</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Install</h3>
        <pre><code>pip install physure==0.1.8</code></pre>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="release">
      <div class="release-header">
        <h2 id="v017">
          <span class="release-version">v0.1.7</span>
          <span class="release-date">2025</span>
        </h2>
      </div>
      <div class="release-body">
        <ul>
          <li>Added JAX backend with full <code>jax.jit</code> and <code>jax.vmap</code> support</li>
          <li>Functional API (<code>physure.functional</code>) for explicit covariance state in JAX pipelines</li>
          <li>FunctionalState registered as a JAX pytree</li>
          <li>Correlated uncertainty propagation via covariance store</li>
          <li><code>propagation_mode</code> context manager to switch modes</li>
          <li>Fixed temperature offset arithmetic (Celsius/Fahrenheit difference returns Kelvin delta)</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="release">
      <div class="release-header">
        <h2 id="v016">
          <span class="release-version">v0.1.6</span>
          <span class="release-date">2025</span>
        </h2>
      </div>
      <div class="release-body">
        <ul>
          <li>PyTorch backend: <code>__torch_dispatch__</code> integration for JIT compilation</li>
          <li>Unit checks at trace time → compiled graph sees only raw tensors (&lt;1.1× overhead)</li>
          <li>NumPy backend with Numba JIT support</li>
          <li>physure grammar interpreter (<code>physure.ext.grammar</code>)</li>
          <li>REPL and CLI entry point (<code>python -m physure</code>)</li>
          <li>SymPy integration for symbolic differentiation</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="release">
      <div class="release-header">
        <h2 id="v015">
          <span class="release-version">v0.1.5</span>
          <span class="release-date">2024</span>
        </h2>
      </div>
      <div class="release-body">
        <ul>
          <li>Rust core (<code>physure-core</code>) via PyO3: RationalUnit, UnitRegistry, CovarianceStore</li>
          <li>Zero-dependency base install — pure Python fallback for all Rust paths</li>
          <li>SI prefix support: all 24 prefixes (yocto to yotta)</li>
          <li>125+ named units across 28 dimensions</li>
          <li>CODATA physical constants module</li>
          <li>Pydantic v2 integration for quantity validation in models</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="release">
      <div class="release-header">
        <h2 id="v010">
          <span class="release-version">v0.1.0</span>
          <span class="release-date">2024</span>
        </h2>
      </div>
      <div class="release-body">
        <p>Initial public release — "The Over-Engineered Homework Validator".</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Core <code>Quantity</code> class with unit-safe arithmetic</li>
          <li>Unit expression parser (/, *, ^, SI prefixes)</li>
          <li>Basic uncertainty propagation (independent errors)</li>
          <li>Temperature offset units (°C, °F, K)</li>
          <li>MIT License</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="callout callout-info" style="margin-top: 2rem;">
    <p>For the full commit history, see the <a href="https://github.com/Alexisrx96/physure/commits/main" target="_blank" rel="noopener">GitHub commits</a>. To report a bug or request a feature, <a href="https://github.com/Alexisrx96/physure/issues" target="_blank" rel="noopener">open an issue</a>.</p>
  </div>
</DocsLayout>

<style>
  .releases { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 0; }

  .release {
    border-left: 2px solid var(--border2);
    padding-left: 1.5rem;
    padding-bottom: 2rem;
    position: relative;
  }
  .release::before {
    content: '';
    position: absolute;
    left: -5px; top: 0.85rem;
    width: 8px; height: 8px;
    border-radius: 50%;
    background: var(--border2);
  }
  .release.current::before { background: var(--accent2); }

  .release-header h2 {
    display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 0.75rem;
    border: none; padding: 0; margin: 0 0 1rem;
  }
  .release-version { font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace; color: var(--text); }
  .release-date { color: var(--text3); font-size: 0.8rem; font-weight: 400; font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif; }
  .release-body h3 { color: var(--text3); font-size: 0.8rem; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.06em; margin: 1rem 0 0.4rem; }
  .release-body ul { margin-bottom: 0.75rem; }
  .release-body pre { margin-top: 0.5rem; }
</style>
